WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:02.866
Ralph Angel:
Previously on
"Queen Sugar"...

00:02.910 --> 00:05.128
I know you're upset.
Please come home.

00:05.170 --> 00:07.786
What home?

00:07.830 --> 00:11.049
- Doctor says I got lupus.
- We gotta tell them.

00:11.090 --> 00:14.218
'Cause we done already seen
what se<_:rets can do
to this family.

00:14.270 --> 00:15.828
You free for dinner
tonight?

00:15.880 --> 00:17.700
Remy:
Whatever game
you're playing,

00:17.750 --> 00:19.706
don't put all your chips
on the table.

00:19.750 --> 00:22.275
We're the only audience
you're peddling alternative
facts to today?

00:22.320 --> 00:25.312
Change requires
that we change, too.

00:25.370 --> 00:27.884
Darla: I can't take Blue away
from the only family
he's ever known.

00:27.940 --> 00:30.101
We're his family, too.

00:42.910 --> 00:44.775
How you feeling, man?

00:56.960 --> 01:00.088
Hollywood:
Bruh, whatever it is
that got you on that boat,

01:00.140 --> 01:02.870
it ain't gonna get no better
till you get it off your chest.

01:06.320 --> 01:09.232
What?
Is it Darla?

01:11.150 --> 01:12.879
Y'all got in a fight?

01:14.500 --> 01:16.718
Everything is gone, 'Wood.

01:16.770 --> 01:19.068
What everything?

01:19.120 --> 01:20.678
What you mean?

01:25.950 --> 01:30.296
Embrace
your thoughts of me...

01:30.350 --> 01:32.215
Can you get Aunt Vi?

01:34.180 --> 01:38.560
And Nova and Charley,
get them together?

01:43.580 --> 01:45.878
I can only say this once.

01:50.710 --> 01:52.792
Okay.

01:52.850 --> 01:54.454
Okay.

01:54.500 --> 02:00.370
If ever your memory
should warm...

02:05.860 --> 02:08.647
[ theme music playing ]

02:08.690 --> 02:12.808
Dreams never die,
take flight, as the
world turns

02:12.870 --> 02:16.124
Dreams never die,
take flight, as the world
turns

02:16.170 --> 02:18.786
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight

02:20.660 --> 02:22.480
Dreams never die

02:27.970 --> 02:32.009
Keep the colors
in the lines

02:32.060 --> 02:34.699
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight.

02:35.890 --> 02:38.973
- Stay on your grind?
- Yeah.

02:39.020 --> 02:41.102
Okay.

02:41.160 --> 02:42.457
I like that.

02:42.510 --> 02:44.717
[ Charley and Remy
chuckle ]

02:49.690 --> 02:53.035
What in the hell
are you doing on my property?

02:54.470 --> 02:55.949
I just wanted
to congratulate you

02:56.000 --> 02:57.513
on getting your mill
up and going.

02:57.560 --> 02:59.562
- You could've called
for that.
- Yeah.

02:59.610 --> 03:03.865
But I also needed
to discuss some business
with Charley.

03:03.920 --> 03:07.822
You know, mill owner
to mill owner.

03:07.880 --> 03:11.702
Anything you have
to say, you can say
in front of Remy.

03:17.150 --> 03:18.538
[ clears throat ]

03:23.500 --> 03:25.843
Actually,
that's okay, Charley.

03:25.900 --> 03:28.414
This will probably
go quicker if I step out.

03:48.270 --> 03:51.171
As I was saying,
I come in peace,

03:51.230 --> 03:53.528
which I think
is mighty big of me,

03:53.580 --> 03:56.663
seeing as you spent
the last few months

03:56.710 --> 04:01.056
poaching 40% of my farmers
from West St. Jo.

04:01.110 --> 04:03.101
[ chuckles ]

04:03.150 --> 04:06.369
You think
the whole world
belongs to you

04:06.420 --> 04:09.457
unless proven
otherwise, right?

04:11.550 --> 04:14.769
What's the point
of teasing them
with fair prices

04:14.810 --> 04:17.290
when you're gonna
go out of business
in a year or two?

04:17.340 --> 04:19.729
You said I've poached
40% of your farmers.

04:19.780 --> 04:23.250
It's actually 50%,
but who's counting?

04:23.300 --> 04:26.030
Plus I already got
your cousin Bennington
on the hook

04:26.090 --> 04:29.253
for his 20,000 acres,
and others will follow.

04:29.310 --> 04:30.607
They're already
sniffing around here.

04:30.660 --> 04:32.309
They're curious.

04:32.350 --> 04:34.568
Just give me
a few more seasons,

04:34.620 --> 04:38.522
I'll have all the farmers
in St. Jo's grinding with me.

04:38.580 --> 04:41.572
Run you and your uncle
out of business.

04:47.500 --> 04:50.719
I have never known
a woman like you before.

04:53.030 --> 04:55.191
You intrigue me.

04:57.900 --> 05:01.028
We'd make
a pretty good team.

05:01.080 --> 05:04.334
I know you've got enough sense
not to let our family's past

05:04.390 --> 05:07.735
get in the way
of making a little money.

05:07.780 --> 05:13.252
_ You're not _
seriously suggesting
that I partner with you?

05:13.310 --> 05:15.778
We could take over
the cane busmess

05:15.830 --> 05:18.264
in the whole damn South.

05:24.010 --> 05:25.750
[ scoffs ]

05:32.240 --> 05:34.629
There is no way

05:34.680 --> 05:38.150
I would ever
do business with you.

05:38.200 --> 05:39.895
Just think about it.

05:39.940 --> 05:41.498
I am thinking about it.

05:43.430 --> 05:45.113
The answer is no.

05:56.310 --> 05:57.914
Good day.

06:12.150 --> 06:13.754
What was that about?

06:17.020 --> 06:19.409
I don't know,
exactly.

06:29.380 --> 06:30.859
Hello, Mr. Prosper.

06:30.910 --> 06:33.162
Come on, Darla,
you should sound
happier than that.

06:33.210 --> 06:34.814
Tomorrow's harvest!

06:34.870 --> 06:38.954
Yeah, been a while
since this place
has seen one.

06:40.220 --> 06:41.608
Ernest would be proud.

06:41.660 --> 06:45.357
Yeah, everything
he worked so hard for--

06:45.400 --> 06:48.779
for Blue and Ralph Angel
to have.

06:48.840 --> 06:52.617
Yep, tell Ralph Angel
I'll be here in the morning.

06:52.670 --> 06:54.490
- Bright and early.
- Yes, sir.

06:54.540 --> 06:55.882
Big day.
[ chuckles ]

06:55.930 --> 06:58.626
Big, big day.
Long time coming.

06:58.670 --> 06:59.807
Ha!

07:02.940 --> 07:05.283
- [ car door closes ]
- [ engine starts ]

07:09.690 --> 07:13.330
- [ door opens, closes ]
-Hmm.

07:15.600 --> 07:18.034
That is gonna
be moved.

07:24.920 --> 07:26.911
War...

07:29.400 --> 07:31.004
Perfect.

07:31.050 --> 07:33.575
And the elephant.

07:48.110 --> 07:49.668
Hello?

07:49.730 --> 07:52.073
Aunt Vi?

07:52.120 --> 07:53.371
Hey.

07:53.420 --> 07:54.944
Sorry I'm late, y'all.

07:56.820 --> 07:59.038
What's going on?

07:59.080 --> 08:01.810
- It's Ralph Angel.
- Something happened
with him and Darla.

08:01.870 --> 08:05.340
- Is he getting cold feet?
- If I knew, I'd tell you.

08:05.390 --> 08:06.914
I don't know,

08:06.960 --> 08:08.518
but he's shook.

08:10.140 --> 08:11.482
[ sighs ]

08:16.800 --> 08:18.745
Ralph Angel,
baby, come here.

08:18.800 --> 08:20.222
Sit down.

08:22.760 --> 08:25.194
I just want to stand up.

08:25.240 --> 08:27.583
That's okay,
I just--

08:27.630 --> 08:29.359
I just need to be
on my feet.

08:29.420 --> 08:30.933
No matter what,
we got your back.

08:30.980 --> 08:32.629
Yeah, we're here
for you, Rah.

08:34.640 --> 08:37.939
I know it can be
a stressful time
leading up to a wedding.

08:37.990 --> 08:39.469
Ain't gonna be
no wedding.

08:39.510 --> 08:41.978
What happened,
Ralph Angel?

08:46.870 --> 08:50.306
[ sighs ]

08:50.350 --> 08:52.523
- It's Blue.
- What did she do
to that baby?

08:52.570 --> 08:54.561
- I told you!
I knew it!
- Is he okay?

08:54.620 --> 08:56.429
- Where is he?
- Ralph Angel,
where is Blue?

08:58.580 --> 08:59.922
Where's Blue?

09:01.620 --> 09:02.882
He's okay.

09:04.580 --> 09:06.184
Um...

09:12.720 --> 09:13.766
He ain't mine.

09:16.070 --> 09:18.982
That's what she said,
she-- she said he ain't mine.

09:20.640 --> 09:24.462
That he ain't my s--
that he ain't my son.

09:38.960 --> 09:41.611
Rah, what do you need?

09:45.840 --> 09:48.400
- Baby, I'm so sorry.
- I don't know.

09:51.320 --> 09:54.016
Oh, baby,
I'm so sorry.

09:55.590 --> 09:58.457
Oh, I'm so sorry.

10:02.770 --> 10:05.238
Oh, I'm so sorry.

10:05.300 --> 10:07.200
I'm so sorry.

10:12.430 --> 10:14.739
[crying ]

10:35.150 --> 10:38.449
[ distant dog barking ]

10:38.500 --> 10:41.367
- [ dishes clattering ]
- [ grill sizzling ]

10:46.990 --> 10:48.548
How's Rah doing?

10:48.600 --> 10:50.727
Violet:
He was still in bed
when I left.

10:51.910 --> 10:53.559
I wanted to stay
in bed, too.

10:53.600 --> 10:55.818
Are we sure
he's up for this today?

10:57.480 --> 10:59.129
Are you up for it,
Aunt Vi?

10:59.180 --> 11:01.216
There's no choice.

11:01.260 --> 11:03.694
There's no choice
in any of this.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.001
Hollywood...

11:06.270 --> 11:08.966
Hollywood is with him.

11:09.010 --> 11:13.276
We just gotta keep our heads,
get through this harvest,

11:13.320 --> 11:15.663
and figure out
what's next.

11:18.540 --> 11:20.098
I'll tell you
one thing, though.

11:21.680 --> 11:24.717
That baby,
he's our child.

11:27.590 --> 11:29.945
- He's our child, period.
- [ door opens ]

11:29.990 --> 11:32.948
- Charley: Hi, good morning.
- Violet: Morning!
Come on in, y'all.

11:32.990 --> 11:34.685
Thank you so much
for coming.

11:34.730 --> 11:37.039
- How you doing, girl?
- [ chatter ]

11:37.080 --> 11:38.388
[ whispering ]

11:40.390 --> 11:41.823
Good morning.

11:43.650 --> 11:45.959
How are you?

11:46.000 --> 11:47.956
I'm a little nervous.

11:48.010 --> 11:49.910
[ chuckles ]

11:49.970 --> 11:53.872
I mean,
it's one thing grinding
other people's cane...

11:55.580 --> 11:58.799
but today is special.

12:00.190 --> 12:03.068
I mean, it's our cane
from Daddy's farm.

12:03.110 --> 12:04.930
It's really happening.

12:07.460 --> 12:09.371
I wish he were here
to see It.

12:11.380 --> 12:12.768
And all these people...

12:14.730 --> 12:19.508
coming to support,
help with the harvest.

12:19.560 --> 12:22.256
Hope everything goes off
without a hitch.

12:33.100 --> 12:34.613
Nova:
How you doing?

12:37.400 --> 12:38.571
I'm here.

12:38.620 --> 12:40.315
That's something.

12:48.110 --> 12:50.158
- [ whistles ]
- [ chatter stops ]

12:55.380 --> 12:56.631
Morning.

12:56.680 --> 12:57.942
Farmers:
Morning.

13:00.120 --> 13:03.510
I wanna thank you all
for coming out today.

13:03.560 --> 13:08.384
Today marks
the first harvest
on Bordelon land and...

13:08.430 --> 13:11.342
going on three years.

13:11.390 --> 13:13.699
Been more than a few times
smce we planted

13:13.740 --> 13:16.561
when I didn't think
we'd get here.

13:16.620 --> 13:19.839
We came through storms,
whitefly...

13:22.010 --> 13:25.275
anything man and God
could put in front of us.

13:27.240 --> 13:28.753
And still...

13:31.200 --> 13:32.588
He leads us through.

13:36.900 --> 13:39.198
I know my mama
would be proud.

13:43.170 --> 13:47.288
And my pop,
Ernest Bordelon.

13:47.340 --> 13:50.036
I was trying
to live out

13:50.090 --> 13:52.820
the vision he saw
for me and Bl--

13:52.870 --> 13:54.212
[ quietly ]
and Blue.

14:00.360 --> 14:02.965
Aanay, uh,
I appreciate y'all.

14:04.660 --> 14:06.400
Eat up.

14:06.450 --> 14:08.406
Got a big day
ahead of us.

14:08.450 --> 14:10.532
[ chatter resumes ]

14:12.850 --> 14:15.717
Hey, you done good.

14:15.760 --> 14:17.364
You gonna make it
through the day.

14:22.420 --> 14:23.978
I got your back.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.768
I only wanted
two things, 'Wood.

14:32.080 --> 14:36.301
To be a good father
and a good farmer.

14:43.310 --> 14:46.097
Gonna try and be
at least one today.

15:07.080 --> 15:08.945
- Hi.
- Hey.

15:08.990 --> 15:11.458
- Need some help with that?
- Oh, no, I'm okay, thank you.

15:13.340 --> 15:15.900
So do you got
somewhere to stay
for the next couple of days

15:15.950 --> 15:17.087
till we're through
with harvest?

15:17.130 --> 15:20.031
Um, I'll be
at my sponsor's.

15:20.090 --> 15:22.308
Until he's ready
to talk.

15:24.050 --> 15:26.132
Um...

15:26.180 --> 15:28.569
Ralph Angel usually
picks up Blue from school

15:28.620 --> 15:31.350
in the afternoon
when I'm at work.

15:31.400 --> 15:33.448
Do you know
if he still--

15:33.490 --> 15:35.879
Well, if you like,
we'll get him.

15:35.930 --> 15:37.704
Vi will pick him up.

15:37.760 --> 15:39.364
Of course.

15:39.410 --> 15:41.230
I'd like for you to.
Thank you.

15:42.850 --> 15:45.193
[ sighs ]
Hollywood...

15:48.860 --> 15:50.543
nothing's changed.

15:50.600 --> 15:54.980
I mean,
nothing has to change.

15:55.040 --> 15:58.419
With all due respect, Darla,
you're smarter than that.

16:02.170 --> 16:04.047
I didn't mean
to hurt you all.

16:05.520 --> 16:07.431
I wanted
just the opposite.

16:09.180 --> 16:11.432
I tried to keep all this
away from you guys.

16:11.490 --> 16:13.048
Why didn't you?

16:13.100 --> 16:15.227
Why didn't you
just keep it to yourself?

16:16.710 --> 16:19.929
My parents came and...

16:19.970 --> 16:23.622
things stirred up
and...

16:23.670 --> 16:27.367
it didn't feel right
to continue to keep this
from him.

16:29.770 --> 16:32.546
I want to be with him
for the rest of my life.

16:34.160 --> 16:36.594
And I just--

16:36.640 --> 16:38.289
I just couldn't go through
with the wedding

16:38.340 --> 16:39.853
without him
knowing everything.

16:42.260 --> 16:44.296
That wouldn't
have been right.

16:44.350 --> 16:48.252
Yeah, well,
ain't none of it right.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.309
Not one damn bit.

16:59.190 --> 17:01.010
[ car door opens ]

17:03.710 --> 17:05.052
[ car door closes ]

17:16.990 --> 17:18.764
[ footstep approach ]

17:27.950 --> 17:29.690
Chaney".

17:33.130 --> 17:37.305
_ _This is all a--
this IS all a nightmare.

17:43.970 --> 17:46.530
Things are
really difficult
right now.

17:48.540 --> 17:53.489
But I want you
to know that my commitment
to this job is unwavering.

17:55.900 --> 17:57.322
And to you.

17:59.600 --> 18:04.947
You've been bold-faced lying
to my whole family...

18:07.730 --> 18:11.291
for nearly seven years.

18:13.440 --> 18:15.783
I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

18:15.830 --> 18:18.822
Yeah, but there's no trust
here anymore, Darla.

18:20.440 --> 18:23.568
I will give you
two weeks' severance.

18:23.620 --> 18:25.269
I'm sorry.

18:27.800 --> 18:29.529
Be gone
within the hour.

18:32.760 --> 18:35.718
[ door opens, slams ]

18:57.260 --> 18:59.478
Charley:
I mean, she acted like
she was actually surprised.

18:59.520 --> 19:01.260
Nova:
You did better
than I would've.

19:01.310 --> 19:04.131
Literally taking
everything I have
not to stir up a potion.

19:04.180 --> 19:06.740
A potion?
Girl, what the--

19:06.790 --> 19:08.189
So how's the day running?

19:08.230 --> 19:11.097
Well, the first cane
will start coming in

19:11.150 --> 19:14.449
after cutting tonight
from our place.

19:14.500 --> 19:16.752
And then processing
begins overnight

19:16.800 --> 19:18.882
and we are
off to the races.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.329
The western half
of St. Jo's cane farms

19:21.370 --> 19:22.974
will start coming in--
first ours,

19:23.030 --> 19:25.191
the final ten after that.

19:25.250 --> 19:27.855
And then_ harvest season
is, uh--

19:27.900 --> 19:30.767
it's almost over.

19:30.820 --> 19:33.163
- You sound sa_d.
- I guess I am a little.

19:33.210 --> 19:37.249
Feels damn good,
despite the Landrys.

19:37.300 --> 19:42.124
- What are they up to now?
- Ugh, I'm not gonna bore you
with their latest antics.

19:42.180 --> 19:45.308
- Trust,
they are acting a fool.
- [ computer chimes ]

19:45.350 --> 19:46.692
I'm not gonna
let them distract me.

19:46.750 --> 19:50.356
I'll keep saying it--
I'm proud.

19:50.400 --> 19:52.834
Well, I like to hear you
keep saying it.

19:54.930 --> 19:57.091
Hey, uh--
hey, I gotta run.

19:57.150 --> 19:58.447
Um, listen.

19:58.500 --> 20:01.276
You have a perfect day.

20:02.460 --> 20:03.882
- Okay?
- Thanks, Nova.

20:05.020 --> 20:06.760
Thanks a lot.

20:09.590 --> 20:11.672
[ clicking ]

20:13.770 --> 20:16.648
Hey, Lizy, I just--
I just got your email.

20:16.690 --> 20:18.078
Who sent it?

20:18.120 --> 20:20.031
Anonymous.
And the IP doesn't
track to a name.

20:20.080 --> 20:21.479
Trust me, I checked.

20:21.520 --> 20:22.680
Regardless, I thought
you should know

20:22.740 --> 20:24.162
someone's out here
pitching a story

20:24.220 --> 20:25.642
about all
the internal issues
at Queen Sugar.

20:25.700 --> 20:27.395
But there_ are
no internal issues.

20:27.440 --> 20:29.305
The fact that there could be
is a provocative pitch.

20:29.350 --> 20:31.261
They claim the place
isn't up to snuff

20:31.310 --> 20:32.914
and that local farmers
are at risk if they
mill out there.

20:32.970 --> 20:34.096
Lies!

20:34.140 --> 20:36.005
Queen Sugar
is completely functional

20:36.060 --> 20:37.743
and has been for
the last couple of months.

20:37.800 --> 20:39.791
Every machine
is damn near new.

20:39.840 --> 20:41.660
This is-- this is someone
slandering my Sister.

20:41.710 --> 20:45.498
This-- this is a family
called the Landrys.

20:45.540 --> 20:47.019
They're slandering
my sister.

20:48.680 --> 20:51.410
Well, if I don't do the story,
someone else will.

20:51.460 --> 20:53.155
Charley's a name.
She's a national voice.

20:53.200 --> 20:54.679
IfI can get her
on the record,

20:54.730 --> 20:56.334
I can try to make sure
it's balanced at least.

20:56.380 --> 20:57.859
Can you deliver her?

21:01.300 --> 21:06.294
Doing the same old thing
and hoping to change

21:06.350 --> 21:08.079
Using the Lord
to make...

21:08.130 --> 21:10.303
An open letter
to the administration

21:10.350 --> 21:13.911
on every locker
at Gardini.

21:13.960 --> 21:17.134
Gotta be the stupidest idea
I've ever heard of.

21:17.180 --> 21:20.183
Why couldn't
we just email everybody?

21:20.230 --> 21:21.959
How'd I let you talk me
into doing this?

21:22.010 --> 21:25.628
Christian, not everybody
looks at their email.

21:25.670 --> 21:28.059
But people will see
their lockers.

21:28.110 --> 21:30.192
- Boy: Those are the guys.
- Boy #2: Man, crazy.

21:30.240 --> 21:32.060
Hey.

21:35.460 --> 21:37.246
- That's him.
- Way to go, Micah.

21:37.290 --> 21:41.420
Let's go now,
it won't be long

21:41.470 --> 21:43.984
- Hold on, hey...
- [ sighs ]

21:44.040 --> 21:45.200
[ school bell rings ]

21:45.260 --> 21:48.343
[ faucet running ]

21:48.390 --> 21:50.119
How you feeling
these days?

21:50.170 --> 21:53.697
Oh, baby,
I'm blessed.

21:53.740 --> 21:55.822
Blessed is the standard
black person's greeting.

21:55.870 --> 21:57.872
That's lovely.

21:57.920 --> 22:00.388
It's really lovely,

22:00.440 --> 22:03.182
but deflects from actually
answering the question.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.609
Girl, what are
you talking about?

22:06.670 --> 22:09.366
We're all blessed.

22:09.410 --> 22:10.581
That's a given.

22:12.330 --> 22:15.015
But I'm here
to check on you.

22:15.070 --> 22:17.231
So I'm asking
how you are feeling.

22:18.680 --> 22:20.728
Beyond blessed,
please.

22:23.950 --> 22:26.555
Well, I'm sad.

22:26.600 --> 22:28.420
[ sighs ]

22:29.820 --> 22:31.776
I wanted...

22:33.390 --> 22:36.211
to be at the farm today
with Ralph Angel,

22:36.260 --> 22:38.342
harvesting his first crop.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.743
Uh-huh.

22:40.790 --> 22:43.520
Wanted to see
that look on his face.

22:43.570 --> 22:45.652
That pride,

22:45.710 --> 22:48.611
- that sense
of accomplishment...
- [ items clatter ]

22:48.670 --> 22:50.353
...from a boy...

22:51.840 --> 22:55.844
that the world
nearly swallowed whole.

22:57.110 --> 23:01.763
I saw everybody
there together

23:01.810 --> 23:04.722
in my mind's eye
so many times.

23:04.770 --> 23:06.374
But we're all here.

23:07.640 --> 23:09.289
That's a blessing.

23:12.820 --> 23:14.685
- Yeah, you're right.
- [ bag zips ]

23:21.350 --> 23:22.521
Nova...

23:25.310 --> 23:27.961
I want to hold Blue.

23:28.010 --> 23:30.968
I raised that baby
from diapers

23:31.010 --> 23:34.923
to kindergarten
like he was my own son.

23:34.970 --> 23:36.972
I remember
his first words.

23:37.020 --> 23:38.533
Aunt Vi?

23:38.590 --> 23:41.013
Papa.

23:41.070 --> 23:42.719
Hoo.
[ chuckles ]

23:42.760 --> 23:44.546
He loved his papa.

23:48.030 --> 23:52.808
I guess I'm glad
Ernest ain't here.

23:52.860 --> 23:57.900
'Cause this
would've robbed him
of what joy he had left.

23:57.950 --> 23:59.736
It was like...

24:05.920 --> 24:08.343
Ralph Angel did
in the past.

24:10.100 --> 24:13.399
You know?
That he could
make such goodness.

24:16.580 --> 24:19.708
I guess good...

24:21.060 --> 24:22.459
doesn't last.

24:23.670 --> 24:25.456
Blue is good.

24:27.420 --> 24:30.674
And whatever
we have with him
will always last.

24:40.600 --> 24:42.340
Amen, baby.

24:42.390 --> 24:44.517
[ phone buzzing ]

24:46.830 --> 24:48.309
I need to take this,
Aunt Vi.

24:48.350 --> 24:49.567
- Excuse me.
- Mm-hmm.

24:54.970 --> 24:57.313
Amen.

24:57.360 --> 24:59.442
Thanks
for calling me back.

24:59.490 --> 25:02.015
No problem, but I don't think
you're gonna like my answer.

25:02.060 --> 25:03.789
Wow, you're
just telling me "no"?

25:03.850 --> 25:05.272
Aren't you the one
who's always telling us

25:05.320 --> 25:07.936
to ask the tough questions,
do the tough story?

25:07.980 --> 25:09.459
Stay true to our
journalistic integrity?

25:09.500 --> 25:11.411
[ stammering ]
Yes, and I'm trying.

25:11.460 --> 25:13.542
I can't publish
a piece based on rumor

25:13.590 --> 25:16.548
about what this
cane dynasty mightdo
to your sister's company.

25:16.600 --> 25:19.592
So slander, intimidation,
and hostile business practices

25:19.640 --> 25:21.426
against the only
black woman mill owner

25:21.470 --> 25:23.597
_in all of Louisiana
isn't newsworthy?

25:23.650 --> 25:25.072
What if you're wrong, Nova?

25:25.130 --> 25:27.257
If you're wrong
and I put this piece
out there,

25:29.520 --> 25:33.217
- Woman: Hi.
- I'm sorry, but, um,
you'll thank me later.

25:33.270 --> 25:34.305
[ line clicks ]

25:35.620 --> 25:36.826
"Thank you later."

25:39.050 --> 25:41.359
Charley:
Mr. Stewart, I really
don't know how to answer that.

25:41.400 --> 25:42.571
Cardale:
Ain't much to it.

25:42.620 --> 25:44.178
Just asked if you had
any breakdowns.

25:44.230 --> 25:45.788
"Yes" or "no"
ought to get it.

25:45.840 --> 25:47.398
No.

25:47.450 --> 25:48.758
Not a one?

25:48.800 --> 25:50.882
Every mill in this parish
and beyond

25:50.940 --> 25:54.103
has had machinery go down
for brief periods of time,

25:54.160 --> 25:57.243
but--
but that's to be expected
when you're running 24/7.

25:57.290 --> 25:59.338
I need to trust you.

25:59.380 --> 26:00.984
And you can.

26:05.690 --> 26:07.999
A number of farmers
in this collective

26:08.040 --> 26:10.031
have already milled
with me this season.

26:12.300 --> 26:15.952
I'm just telling you
what folks are saying,
Miss Charley.

26:16.000 --> 26:19.618
Down at the feed store,
the bank.

26:19.660 --> 26:23.130
Folks even talking about it
right here at High Yellow.

26:23.190 --> 26:24.919
- Where are you
getting this from?
- Doesn't matter.

26:24.970 --> 26:27.530
If someone is spreading lies
about me and my business,

26:27.580 --> 26:29.093
hell, yes, it matters.

26:35.940 --> 26:40.809
Have we had our share
of interruptions? Yes.

26:40.860 --> 26:44.546
A choke here or there,
but-- but you and I
both know that...

26:44.600 --> 26:46.591
that's normal.

26:46.640 --> 26:48.949
Please just come down
and see for yourself.

26:48.990 --> 26:51.948
You are
your father's daughter.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.958
- You got spirit!
- [ chuckles ]

26:55.000 --> 26:57.389
And I respect that.
I do.

27:00.790 --> 27:04.658
and I got workers that need
to be paid by day's end.

27:04.710 --> 27:08.396
I can't afford
to have you shut down
for one reason or another.

27:08.450 --> 27:10.964
- My mill has all
of its certifications.
- I know.

27:11.020 --> 27:13.363
We_ have-- we have run
Without any problem.

27:13.410 --> 27:15.628
I assure you
that there's...

27:15.670 --> 27:17.149
Good luck to you.

27:27.990 --> 27:30.686
Farmer:
I'm telling you, man,
your sister's in trouble.

27:30.730 --> 27:32.595
And she don't want
you to know it.

27:32.650 --> 27:34.129
Now, Jacob said
Kev went up there

27:34.170 --> 27:36.638
just this morning
and nothing's running.

27:36.690 --> 27:39.341
That's bullshit,
man.

27:39.390 --> 27:42.302
That's Landry and Boudreaux
just spreading their nonsense.

27:42.350 --> 27:45.649
Come this Thursday,
I'll have a truckload
full of harvested cane

27:45.700 --> 27:48.965
that'll be worthless
if it ain't grinded ASAP.

27:49.010 --> 27:51.615
Can't be
no machine problems.

27:51.670 --> 27:53.570
This is my life.

27:55.890 --> 27:57.312
I feel you.

27:59.240 --> 28:01.401
Worst-case scenario,

28:01.460 --> 28:05.419
I'm looking
at three units of loss
per day on uncut cane.

28:05.460 --> 28:08.452
20 or 30% loss in value
ifI leave it in the ground.

28:08.510 --> 28:10.853
- So you gonna
keep cutting?
- Damn right.

28:10.900 --> 28:14.984
First, there ain't
no problems

28:15.040 --> 28:17.998
and I ain't scared
of no Landrys.

28:18.040 --> 28:22.124
Second, I'm inside
the insurance differential
we Signed With y'all.

28:22.170 --> 28:23.694
All right?

28:25.520 --> 28:30.651
Hey, man, don't
let them white boys
get in your head.

28:30.700 --> 28:33.965
Don't let them run you away
from no good thing.

28:34.010 --> 28:35.523
Stand up to them.

28:37.320 --> 28:39.049
You got this.

28:43.330 --> 28:44.752
[ chattering ]

28:44.810 --> 28:46.459
[ sighs ]

28:56.160 --> 28:58.242
- [ school bell rings ]
- [ chatter ]

29:03.350 --> 29:04.829
Micah, have a seat.

29:21.710 --> 29:24.235
You've made quite a stir
publishing that letter.

29:24.280 --> 29:27.408
I've already received
numerous calls from trustees

29:27.460 --> 29:31.806
who are effectively
my bosses.

29:31.850 --> 29:34.808
These things
have been accepted
for a very long time

29:34.860 --> 29:36.725
because they're part
of our history.

29:36.770 --> 29:40.069
Yeah, yes,
Dr. Shore, but...

29:40.120 --> 29:44.033
symbols of a shameful past
shouldn't be displayed

29:44.080 --> 29:45.638
in a position of honor.

29:45.690 --> 29:47.738
You made that quite clear
in your letter.

29:49.520 --> 29:53.172
Have you ever read much
of John Adams?

29:53.220 --> 29:56.951
He said the jaws of power
are always open to devour,

29:57.010 --> 30:00.229
stretched out to destroy
the freedom of thinking,

30:00.270 --> 30:03.444
speaking, and writing.

30:03.490 --> 30:06.015
Right, but...

30:06.060 --> 30:08.699
that kind of make it--
makes it sound like

30:08.760 --> 30:10.489
it was okay to write
what I wrote.

30:10.540 --> 30:13.839
Freedom of speech
is a friend of change,

30:13.890 --> 30:16.154
and we needed that change
around here.

30:16.200 --> 30:18.418
I wanted you to be
the first to know

30:18.460 --> 30:20.371
the sword
will be removed

30:20.420 --> 30:22.809
along with the other
Confederate artifacts.

30:22.860 --> 30:24.760
But the school board
took issue

30:24.820 --> 30:27.288
with your unapproved
posting of that letter

30:27.340 --> 30:30.161
on school property.

30:30.210 --> 30:33.338
In their eyes,
it's vandalism.

30:33.390 --> 30:37.121
The decision was
suspension for 30 days.

30:37.180 --> 30:41.389
- A month?
- There's a fine line here,
Micah.

30:41.440 --> 30:43.135
And you crossed it.

30:43.180 --> 30:46.001
Next time,
be more careful.

30:48.410 --> 30:50.139
[ footsteps ]

30:50.190 --> 30:52.146
Blue:
Do you think Pop
would take me to Italy?

30:52.190 --> 30:53.976
Or Mommy?

30:54.020 --> 30:56.409
I'm sure they would.

30:57.980 --> 31:00.710
But what if me
and your Aunt Vi
took you?

31:00.770 --> 31:02.988
Then I could go, too!

31:03.030 --> 31:04.634
I like that idea.

31:05.860 --> 31:06.986
Auntie Nova!

31:07.030 --> 31:09.112
Mmm, hey...

31:09.170 --> 31:10.728
my little Blue bear!

31:13.430 --> 31:14.988
How's school?

31:15.040 --> 31:17.349
- My teacher showed us
pictures of Italy.
- Oh.

31:17.390 --> 31:19.563
She says they have
really good pizzas.

31:19.610 --> 31:23.080
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. I'd eat pizzas
every day.

31:23.140 --> 31:25.779
You sure you wouldn't miss
your Aunt Vi's cooking?

31:25.840 --> 31:28.741
Violet:
Who wouldn't miss
my cooking?

31:30.450 --> 31:34.921
I mean, yeah, of course
I'm gonna miss your cooking.

31:34.980 --> 31:38.757
You're the best chef
in the entire world.

31:40.240 --> 31:42.060
In the entire world,
Blue?

31:42.110 --> 31:44.158
- Yeah, I know for sure.
- Oh.

31:44.200 --> 31:45.246
You heard him.

31:45.290 --> 31:46.769
[ giggles ]

31:46.810 --> 31:48.949
[ Blue mumbles ]

31:48.990 --> 31:52.721
Okay, so, what is
your favorite meal?

31:52.780 --> 31:55.726
'Cause I'm gonna cook
whatever you want tonight.

31:55.780 --> 31:58.681
Anything I want?
Like, anything?

31:58.740 --> 31:59.957
Anything.

32:01.780 --> 32:05.216
I want the wings
fried up in the pan.

32:05.270 --> 32:07.488
- Extra crispy.
- Hollywood: Mm.

32:07.530 --> 32:10.613
Also with
the honey barbecue sauce.

32:10.660 --> 32:13.743
Lots and lots
of sauce.

32:13.800 --> 32:16.360
Got it. Okay, so now,
what about the sides?

32:19.020 --> 32:22.490
[ Blue and Violet sigh ]

32:22.540 --> 32:26.328
Okay... Ithink
I'm gonna go

32:26.370 --> 32:29.589
with the red beans
mixed up with the rice
mixed up with shrimp.

32:29.640 --> 32:31.028
All mixed up together.

32:31.070 --> 32:33.118
Nova:
All mixed up
together.

32:33.160 --> 32:35.947
And can I not have
any greens?

32:35.990 --> 32:38.129
Boy, that's the best part!

32:39.560 --> 32:41.903
Hollywood, hush.

32:41.960 --> 32:45.088
This _is Blue's
speCIal meal.

32:45.130 --> 32:48.042
- You got no say.
- [ Blue chuckles ]

32:48.090 --> 32:49.739
I'll allow you to have
a piece, okay?

32:49.790 --> 32:51.439
Thank you.

32:51.490 --> 32:53.913
My tummy's ready,
Auntie Vi.

32:53.970 --> 32:56.962
- Oh!
- [ chuckles ]

32:59.360 --> 33:01.442
Charley on phone:
Hi, you've reached
Charley Bordelon.

33:01.500 --> 33:02.922
I can't get to the phone
right now,

33:02.980 --> 33:04.322
so please leave
a message.

33:04.370 --> 33:06.884
- [ beeps ]
- Yo, what's up, Charley?

33:06.940 --> 33:09.283
You know
what's g0ing on
at the mill.

33:09.330 --> 33:12.504
Rumors flying,
nobody picking up.

33:12.550 --> 33:13.983
Hit me back.

33:16.250 --> 33:18.889
- [ phone clicking ]
- [ sighs ] Come on, Remy.

33:20.250 --> 33:22.206
[ line ringing ]

33:22.260 --> 33:23.943
Remy:
Hey, you've reached
Remy Newell.

33:24.000 --> 33:25.865
- Can't get to the phone
right now...
- Damn!

33:29.310 --> 33:31.471
Ain't like them
to not call me back.

33:32.610 --> 33:35.090
Something
don't feel right.

33:35.140 --> 33:37.529
I left messages
for Charley, too.

33:40.100 --> 33:42.056
[ sighs ]
Well, maybe something
isgoing on.

33:42.100 --> 33:43.488
You know what it is.

33:43.540 --> 33:47.055
Them Boudreaux boys
up to no good.

33:47.110 --> 33:49.408
Come on, now.

33:49.460 --> 33:53.453
Well, we all saw
the splinter go down
at ribbon cutting.

33:55.200 --> 33:57.111
I don't know,
maybe...

34:00.730 --> 34:03.164
Maybe she's moving
too fast on this.

34:04.820 --> 34:07.607
You know, I'm looking
at truckloads of cane sitting

34:07.650 --> 34:10.289
and you can't even
get your-- your mill
on the phone.

34:10.350 --> 34:12.989
- I know.
- And what--
what does Darla say?

34:14.480 --> 34:16.528
She's sitting
right outside
of the office.

34:16.570 --> 34:18.561
Where does she say
Charley is?

34:21.620 --> 34:23.520
Excuse me.

34:23.580 --> 34:25.059
Ralph A--

34:37.460 --> 34:39.246
Nova:
If Lizy doesn't write this,

34:39.290 --> 34:41.508
someone else _
that's less friendly Will.

34:41.550 --> 34:45.816
This way, I can at least
have some control
over the story.

34:45.860 --> 34:47.555
She's a friend.

34:50.780 --> 34:53.032
You talk to the other farmers
and you do this article,

34:53.090 --> 34:54.569
_We can_ turn this
into a piece about

34:54.610 --> 34:57.124
how you're being treated
by the Landrys,

34:57.180 --> 35:00.616
about the systematic racism
against black farmers
and now you,

35:00.660 --> 35:03.094
the only black mill owner
in the state.

35:03.140 --> 35:05.313
We can fight this.

35:07.060 --> 35:08.834
You can turn it around.

35:11.760 --> 35:14.058
After this, there'll be
something else.

35:15.240 --> 35:17.401
Something after that.

35:22.550 --> 35:26.850
I mis_calculated
their greed.

35:26.900 --> 35:27.980
Remy:
Fine.

35:28.030 --> 35:30.248
But now it's time
to do new math.

35:31.950 --> 35:33.906
Now we got to get out
to the remaining farms

35:33.950 --> 35:36.601
and talk to folks
together.

35:36.650 --> 35:40.177
'Cause sitting here
is nothing but a pity party.

35:40.220 --> 35:43.656
One of the greatest gifts
you got from your father
is your fight.

35:45.230 --> 35:47.698
Both of you.

35:47.750 --> 35:51.538
Charley, fight back.

35:55.100 --> 35:57.239
Yeah, I'll fight,
all right.

35:58.540 --> 36:00.679
Good.
Which farm first?

36:00.720 --> 36:03.234
If you could handle
the remaining farms
on your own,

36:03.290 --> 36:04.541
that would
help me out.

36:04.590 --> 36:06.717
Happy to do it.

36:06.770 --> 36:08.249
Thank you.

36:09.640 --> 36:11.460
And, Nova,
you're right.

36:11.510 --> 36:14.331
I should talk to your friend,
set the record straight.

36:15.600 --> 36:18.342
But I need to make
a stop first.

36:18.390 --> 36:20.039
Where are you going?

36:20.090 --> 36:21.648
To the source.

36:28.010 --> 36:30.262
What it is, bro?

36:30.310 --> 36:32.653
Everybody's spooked.

36:32.710 --> 36:34.439
All the rumors
about the mill.

36:36.230 --> 36:39.051
- What's going on?
- Everything is fine, man.

36:39.100 --> 36:40.715
The mill is fine.

36:40.760 --> 36:42.796
That's just the Landrys
using fear tactics,

36:42.850 --> 36:45.318
trying to get back
the business they lost,
that's all.

36:47.500 --> 36:50.719
I got more cane
coming off them fields
early morning

36:50.770 --> 36:52.897
and Charley
ain't answering my calls.

36:52.940 --> 36:55.113
She went to see
the Landrys face-to-face.

36:55.160 --> 36:57.162
We've been talking
to them.

36:57.210 --> 36:58.199
How'd that work out?

37:00.210 --> 37:02.121
[ sighs deeply ]

37:02.170 --> 37:03.990
It ain't gonna change.

37:04.040 --> 37:05.826
It's personal.

37:05.870 --> 37:09.044
It ain't_about harvest
and they ain't gonna give up.

37:09.090 --> 37:12.139
Not till they get
that land back.

37:13.270 --> 37:16.091
Well, look here,

37:16.140 --> 37:18.791
don't worry.

37:18.840 --> 37:20.967
Your sister knows
What she's doing.

37:22.540 --> 37:24.235
She'll figure it out.

37:30.240 --> 37:32.800
[ distant chatter ]

37:36.070 --> 37:39.028
[ door creaks open ]

38:05.370 --> 38:09.750
Well, so much
for privacy.

38:09.800 --> 38:13.065
I won't tell
anybody anything
you don't want me to say.

38:15.680 --> 38:19.411
But since I'm here
and I know...

38:21.560 --> 38:22.948
Lupus can be rough.

38:24.780 --> 38:26.816
But it can also
be managed.

38:31.220 --> 38:33.029
Yesterday was bad.

38:34.310 --> 38:35.823
Today was better.

38:37.570 --> 38:41.836
And to-tomorrow hopefully
Will be better still.

38:44.360 --> 38:46.408
I'm gonna put you
on my own regimen.

38:46.450 --> 38:48.668
The organic route.

38:48.710 --> 38:50.575
Nature's medicine.

38:53.980 --> 38:55.629
Double duty.

38:58.550 --> 39:00.199
Yes.

39:02.900 --> 39:05.073
Thank you,
Dr. Bordelon.

39:05.120 --> 39:06.508
Doctor...
[ chuckles ]

39:06.560 --> 39:09.199
I'll be here,
but you decide

39:09.250 --> 39:11.298
Yeah, you decide

39:11.340 --> 39:15.344
When you wanna
fall into my arms

39:15.390 --> 39:19.599
Fall into my arms

